address: 51 Kensington Church Street, London W8 4BA, United Kingdom
author: Olvia C.
description:
VIBE: 
Super comfortable inviting restaurant with delicious homey food.

FOOD:
Grilled avacado - yummy, the pesto sauce that came with it was really good

Fish & chips - fish was super good, crunchy on the out side and the fish was perfectly cooked. However I was not a fan of the thick dense fries.

Chocolate cheese cake - not good, it taste grainy with a weird texture. I only ate the ice cream.

Toffee cake - good, but really strong toffee flavor. If u don't like toffee or strong flavors in general I would avoid this.
